This repository contains two mobile website projects built for practicing HTML and CSS. Both projects are designed to create a responsive mobile website, but each uses a different approach for styling:

Project 1: Styled with Vanilla CSS

Project 2: Styled with Tailwind CSS

Both projects are designed to help you understand the differences between writing custom CSS and using a utility-first CSS framework like Tailwind.
Project Descriptions
Project 1: Mobile Website with Vanilla CSS
This project is a mobile-responsive website built using HTML and CSS. The focus is on writing custom CSS to style the website from scratch. It includes:

A responsive layout for mobile devices.

Custom CSS for styling components like buttons, navigation, and cards.

Media queries for responsiveness.

Features:
Responsive design for mobile screens.

Custom CSS for styling.

Basic HTML structure.

Technologies Used:
HTML

CSS

Project 2: Mobile Website with Tailwind CSS
This project is a mobile-responsive website built using HTML and Tailwind CSS. The focus is on using Tailwind's utility classes to style the website quickly and efficiently. It includes:

A responsive layout for mobile devices.

Tailwind CSS classes for styling components.

Predefined utility classes for responsiveness.

Features:
Responsive design for mobile screens.

Tailwind CSS for styling.

Basic HTML structure.

Technologies Used:
HTML

Tailwind CSS
ow to Run the Projects
Prerequisites
A modern web browser (e.g., Chrome, Firefox, Safari).

A code editor (e.g., VS Code, Sublime Text).

Steps to Run
Clone the repository
Navigate to the project folder
Open the index.html file in your browser.

